<table width='92%' cellpadding='5' cellborder='0'><tr>
	 <td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2'><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> Friday April 13, 2001</td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>REJOICE I TELL YOU!</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Since the dawn of EverQuest one thing has always been asked for - and now it is coming!<P> The test server now has a slide-bar for stackable purchases!  This means that you can now purchase up to 20 water, bread, gems, metal bars, etc at one time.  All stackable items can now be purchased this way.<P> The usual test-disclaimer applies, but this new change should go to the live servers next patch hopefully. 	</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:baelish@castersrealm.com'>Baelish</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 8:31 PM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>FOR SHOW ONLY</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Confused by the name, a player submitted a question to Absor regarding the Ceremonial Wedding Sword. Absor responded stating that this weapon is intented to not have stats as it's only purpose is to look nice while equipped. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3397'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:19 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>BOLTS, NO DROP, AND YOU!</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>A player submitted a comment to the Developer's Corner today regarding the bolt spell animation as well as an idea for 'No Drop' items. Absor responded stating that despite being a cool effect, there are no plans to have the bolt effect added. He also stated that any way to transfer or sell a 'No Drop' item defeats the purpose of 'No Drop' and thus will not be implemented. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3396'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:17 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>WHERE ARE MY SPELLS?</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>In response to a players question regarding the location of Kunark's level 55 spells, Absor posted a quote from the EQ 'spell guy' that stated these spells can only be found in Kunark due to the research of different magic in different parts of the world. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3395'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:13 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>BLINDED BY THE NERF</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Absor took a moment to respond to a players comment on todays Developer's Corner discussion boards regarding the change to the bind sight spell. Despite the unintentional nerf, Absor quoted the spell guru of Verant and stated that there is no intention to return it to it's former functionality. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3394'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:10 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>NO WARRANT REQUIRED</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>A player submitted a question to the Developer's Corner today regarding the reason why there is no option to remove the option for players to inspect you. Alan responded stating that the inspect is not an 'invasive' action and that there is no reason for players to be disturbed by it. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3393'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:08 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>ECONOMIES DISCUSSION CONTINUES</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Absor continued to respond to comments sent into the Developer's Corner discussion boards regarding the server economy discussion. This time Absor clarified his ideas regarding item decay and corpse loss, as well as responded to a few new ideas from players. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3392'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:03 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2'><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> Thursday April 12, 2001</td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>MORE ON BAKING CHANGES</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>In response to the baking changes on Test Server, a player queried Absor regarding some of the specifics of the changes. Absor answered to the best of his knowledge but also stated that this would be undergoing a period of tweaking on the Test server and will be changing. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3391'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 3:04 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>TEST SERVER UPDATE</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>The Test server has recently been updated with some new changes. A very large change to baking and food consumption is included, as well as a change to monk carry weight and some interface and graphical tweaks. Remember, this is only on the <i>Test</i> server and some changes may not be seen on the live servers. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3390'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 3:00 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>CLASS TALKS NOT FORGOTTEN</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Alan posted to todays Developer's Corner message boards to assure players that internal discussions were still being continued with the 'Class Talk' threads. He also stated that ideas from these threads will continue to be implemented over time. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3389'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:55 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>YOU CAN RUN BUT YOU CAN'T HIDE!</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>In response to a recent discussion regarding creatures walking through walls, a player suggested that this be fixed so that players can hide from creatures in certain situations. Absor stated that such a thing is just not possible with the current game limitations. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3388'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:53 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>IN A PANIC</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>A player pointed out to Alan a bug where no success message is given with the current panic animal spell. Alan stated that this will be added soon. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3387'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:51 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>MORE ON TRADE CONTAINERS</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Absor continued the discussion on trade containers today, giving players a few tips on using them as well as verifying a current bug with ovens and that it will soon be fixed. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3386'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 2:49 AM</span></p></td>
