  <td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2'><img border='0' src='/images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> Wednesday April 11, 2001</td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>CANNIBALIZE UPGRADES ON TEST</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Shamans will be pleased to know that some upgrades to the Cannibalize line are currently being reviewed on the Test Server.<p> The changes are as follows: <ul> <li><b>Cannibalize 2:</b> Will Give 33 - 36 mana instead of 28 - 33.</li> <li><b>Cannibalize 3:</b> Will Give 39 - 41 mana instead of 36 - 38.</li> </ul> Note: These changes are only on the Test Server and may change before going live, or not go live at all. 	</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:baelish@castersrealm.com'>Baelish</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 11:02 PM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'>&nbsp;</td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
</tr>
  <tr>
	<td valign='top' align='left' class='news' width='90%'><p class='boldheader'>BARD CHAINS INTENTIONAL</p><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>A confused bard queryed the Developer's Corner today regarding the state of bard snares and why they do not strip SoW from creatures. Absor explained that this was intentional as players requested this change. 	</font>
<br><br><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>Click <a href='viewarticle.asp?Article=3384'><b>here</b></a> for details.</font>
	<p class='newsig'><span class='newsig'>Submitted by </span><span class='newsiglink'><a class='newsiglink' href='mailto:kivlan@castersrealm.com'>Kivlan</a></span><span class='newsig'>, 4:13 AM</span></p></td>
	<td valign='top' align='left'></td>
  </tr>
